well guys, summer is finally here...
Im so excited. But! my summer scedule is so busy. Everyday of the week im busy. Whether it be work, volleyball, basketball, or conditioning. Sorry i havent updated in a while. I just kind of find these things to be pointless because no body even comments on them that much (on my lj at least). Since everynight i lay on the couch and watch TV, ive found two new favorite shows. On channel 107 Noggin...they are Degrassi and Radio Free Roscoe(RFR). Im like obsessed with them now. But not more than the OC. I need to watch the 1st season soon...i havent finished it. Im so glad that the 2nd season is re-playing over the summer! Now i can see the episodes that i missed. I cant believe im saying this, but i missed the finale!!! UGHHH!!  but its okay, i missed it because it was my sisters graduation. ahh! its so weird that shes graduating! i wont see her at school anymore... oh well. I want to make this summer the best summer ive had in a long time. Its gonna be hard though, considering that my two close friends have both left town for the WHOLE summer. blah. its okay, me and hollie are hangin out quite a bit almost every weekend. YESSSSS. boy scoping..what else. we've decided that boys are immature, and that they have cooties and that they need to grow some balls...or somethin like it. but yeah, so this is all on my mind...if i have anything else ill post summore...bye!

~stroma

um...we lost the regional game...enough said.it was a good game, ashley im really sry that we lost because I knew that you wanted it so bad, and most of us did, I just wish had it to do over again. but besides that, nothing really has been going on. I can't wait until school lets out. Im really tired and exhausted. Now that sottball is over, I have to pipe down and try harder on getting strait A's. Let's see, today at school felt like it was really short. I checked out after 1st hour because I wasn't feeling very well, then I came back to school during lunch because I couldn't miss half a day of school or I wouldnt be allowed to play in the game. When I came back, it was field day from then on until school was over. It was pretty boring. Nothing major. Then after the softball game me and my mom went riding everywhere. We figured out where Michelle lives...so BAM. We are all comin for you Michelle and rolling your house. You can count on it. 
       My little poodle, Lady, was limping Sunday night and we took her to the vet the next day. She was walking crooked and stumbled a lot. Then we found out that she either has a brain tumour or she had a stroke, which is really sad for me, because I've had this dog since I was a little girl. I can't remember when i DIDNT have her. They gave us some medicine to give her and she seems a lot better. Everyone please pray for her! Tomorrow im going to watch Starkey's regional game. Good luck ladies. After that me and Hollie and maybe Alyssa are gonna go hang out. Then, out comes the goods for a lonnnnnng night of fun! Heads up Michelle... ;-) Anyways, i just found out that im going on a cruise this summer for our vacation. It's gonna be sweet.

well youz guys, i went to disney world for spring break! It was so mich fun! We arrived late Monday and did whatever at the hotel. Then the rest of the week everybody went to bed around 1:30-2 every mornin, then we had to get up around 7:30 that same morning. This was everyday may I add. Im so tired right now. (im in online) But anyways, I met Mickey Mouse and a bunch of other characters, and i road tower of terror with Yagini, my dad, and Alyssa. I bought the picture. It was priceless. I also road rockin roller coaster with Katie, Alyssa, and Mr. Greg. That was so much fun. On Friday, me, Michelle, ALyssa, coach, Hollay!, and Bethany all went to three parks in 7 hrs. because that was the last day we were there. We went to animal kingdom first. They forced me to ride the dinosaur ride (may i mention that i do not like dinosaurs) and i was attached to Michelle the whole time. She bought the picture. Ill see if i can get a copy and post it...its hilarious. We also played some games in a tournament. We won 2 and lost 2. We should have won all of them but the umpires were pretty bad. We also got to take pictures with the atlanta Braves while they were practicing. Their practice fields were right next to our tournament fields. It was awesome. On the way back to Baton Rouge, me and hollay! watched a bunch of movies and listened to a lot of music. It was fun. That was a long drive...12 hrs..dang. Next year we better fly! Well, that's all of my spring break for youz guys... sorry i havent posted in a while! talk to youz guys later! comment on what yall did for the break...i havent talked to anyone yet since ive gotten back. :-)

~stroma
